You can easily create your auto clicker by recording on the running app. And adjusting the automatically-prepared items extends the macro with recognizing image to deal with various situations such as flexible network load or multiple scenes.
Your own automatic operation button will be easily created.

- Easy record/replay touches on app, by the button of floating console
- Console shows/hides depending on playable records for current app
- The timing and/or content of touches can be branched by image matching

With FRep2 Unlock Key, the unlimited number of records & Tasker plugin are available.

Usage Example
- Recording analog Tap/Swipe/Flick operations for automatic process/scroll/gesture.
- Preload delayed or continuous pushing in prospect of processing delay, such as CPU load or network communication.
- Avoid blind area or blurring by your finger and/or its shadow.
- Combination with automation App through FRep2 replay shortcut/Tasker plugin.
- Demonstrate your App in actual device.


= Notice =
- This app uses Accessibility Service (ACCESSIBILITY_SERVICE) to replay touch operations, to show the replay process, and to detect current app for responsive switching function of floating console.
- Full network access permission is used only for communication with the setup process (Precision mode) in localhost.
- Do not record including personal information and/or password.
- The replay result may differ depending on the load of your device / app. To make good reproducibility, take longer delay for processing wait, stop touch at end point for dragging/flick, and more, try editing sequence to add controls to wait the timing to replay.
